OL,4,Csentence increased by Court of Appeal
OL,6,FStephen Moses KC, for Van-Pooss, said
OL,7,Fthe targeting was "a matter of moments
OL,8,Frather than pre-meditated".
OL,10,FVan-Pooss also pleaded guilty to
OL,11,Fupskirting another woman at the pub
OL,12,Fwhere he worked the day before he
OL,13,Fkilled Ms Knights.
OL,15,FAfter she reported this, Van-Pooss was
OL,16,Fdismissed on August 22 2023, and he
OL,17,Fleft, carrying a backpack with a
OL,18,Fchef's knife inside.
